text:
this week has been a difficult one for us discipline wise, and it all started because i felt too lazy to go grocery shopping last saturday. now i donâ€™t really like grocery shopping but it is so important. when i neglect this it makes it really hard for us to not spend money eating out. we went over budget $40 which we will deduct from this weekâ€™s envelopes, but it impacts so much more than money. we feel bad (physically and emotionally) when we donâ€™t have healthy good food and we are always eating out. we feel bad when we donâ€™t have food for lunches and either go without or buy something. and it starts to impact other areas as well. we have not been on a good sleep pattern this week. going to bed too late and rushing out the door. not taking time to make the right things our priority. but the good thing about friday is it means the end of one week of bad habits and the chance to change this for next week. i find it is in taking responsibility and doing the things we donâ€™t want that we find real freedom and peace of mind. can anyone else relate to this? happy friday all, hereâ€™s to a fresh new week.
.

.

text:
we need to as a society begin to teach younger men and men in general to know how to control themselves. 
i'm tired of hearing "men think with their penises" as an excuse for rapey behaviour. 
men don't think with their penises, they think with their heads and their heads tell them that if they can't control themselves, society would not hold them accountable
.
we need to create a better society for the next generation of nigerian women and girls where we can move at night without the fear of rape. 
where we are not at war with our bodies. 
where we don't hate our bodies because they bring unwanted touch from slimy men
.
let's do better and teach men that no woman's body is their exclusive property. 
let's hold men accountable because in my almost twenty years, i've never heard anyone say "she thinks with her vagina" as an excuse for rape. 
enough said
.
.
.

text:
â€ªone of the greatest current issues is lack of value for life. itâ€™s not just children. it rears itâ€™s head in human trafficking, racism, mass shootings, abuse, and so much more. worldwide there is a lack of value for human life. people become items/objects to be used or disposed of, instead human beings created to be loved. â€¬

we are not apes, wild animals, nor objects. we are made in the image of god and each person of significant worth. when we know how much god values us, all human life-it changes the way we treat others. 
people are not objects to be used. 
people are not commodities to be sold. 
people are not pleasure centers to be exploited. 
people are not punching bags to be abused. 
people are not images to be lusted over.

text:
she was under â€œgreat psychological pressureâ€ 
chris brown was accused of violently raping a girl earlier this week in paris. he was arrested and detained until police came to the conclusion that there was not enough evidence to charge brown. while the investigation is still ongoing, parisian authorities are having a difficult timee believing the accuserâ€™s story. she claims brown brought her into a secluded area and raped her. she then says she left that room and was raped again in a second room. finally, the accuser claims she left that room and was assaulted a third time. police find it odd that the young lady was sexually abused three separate times and never tried to call for help, raise an alarm, or escape. 
now, according to tmz, the alleged victimâ€™s lawyer frank serfati told the associated press thursday (january 24) that his client â€œwas not pressured physicallyâ€ into having sex with bown. she insists that â€œnon-consensual sexâ€ allegedly took place though, and that she was under â€œgreat psychological pressureâ€ during the interaction. serfati continued on to claim brown â€œcornered her in a room that was lockedâ€ and that â€œthere were forced sexual relationsâ€ with â€œonly with men, older men, men who you imagine to be buff.â€ brownâ€™s bodyguard was also detained and released in connection with the alleged assault. 
meanwhile, chris is maintaining his innocence. he has has now hit the woman with a defamation lawsuit and is putting his innocence on the forefront, quite literally, with new merchandise. in a since-deleted instagram post, chris wrote â€œthis bitch lyinâ€ in his caption and heâ€™s now taken those three words and plastered them on some t-shirts. according to the blast the original term was coined when chris was accused of assaulting model baylee curran back in 2016 and now heâ€™s found another way to bring it back to light again. 
the shirts are being sold online through chrisâ€™ black pyramid clothing line, going for $38 a piece. peep the details in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com what do you guys think? #chrisbrown #chrisbrownofficial #chrisbrownworld #chrisbrownfans #thisbitchlyin #metoo #chrisbrownart #breezy #chrisbreezy #teambreezy #undecided

text:
this reminds me: when we were living in ca, and the boys were 4 and 5, we had a neighbor friend named ethan. ethan was zen, reasonable and kind, this gentle vietnamese little buddha of a guy. i would always offer ethan food and more food and he would politely decline. when i kept asking, he would say so wisely: â€œmaggie, no means no.â€ and i would just love it(without knowing why). and i would repeat it and still chide him to eat more than he wanted, just so i could hear him say it again.
but see, when you grow up surrounded by people who do not listen when you say noâ€¦.who pretend you did not say it or attack you for saying it, you do not learn about the boundary of no. so, tiny little ethan was my first model of healthy boundaries via the direct statement of â€œnoâ€. no is a complete sentence and it is not mean, or a crime.
give it a try. you are welcome. now, i am your life coach.

text:
swipe left>>>>> it's not just fun and games!
video games are a favorite past time for many young people. in fact, we often hear parents talk about going to bed and allowing their kids to stay up till the wee hours of the morning playing video games because they think there is inherent safety in them simply being in the house. well that might have been true with the video games from years ago, but nowadays, a video game console is the equivalent of a party line with built in tracking capabilities! your kids can literally be contacted by someone on the other side of the world or across the street. and, you'll never know who they're communicating with if you don't take the time to learn about the gaming console's chat features and location services. predators can cozy up to your child through their favorite video game and groom them right under your nose. before you know it, your child is being lured out of your home to go meet the new friend they met in their favorite games' chat room. so while parents may have no interest in their child's video game, keep in mind that video games are the new playground for predators. pay attention....it's not just fun and games anymore! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #mlk ğŸ“¸:pixaby

text:
being alone on this travel has been a gift.Â Â a scary, wonderful gift. i can no longer follow anything other than my gut, who has alerted me to so much inauthenticity and helped me dodge more loss. when the switch comes on and there is light in our darkness, we then live in tension waiting to change. we fear becoming fearless. we become weak thinking of how strong we are. we fumble and doubt our own sacred knowing...
.
.
i am afraid. i am afraid of becoming whole because my life was built to sanctify how weak and worthless i have felt. i had everything in place to master a great appearance, and stumble through the authentic hunger for connection, being known, and being loved.
.
i am afraid that my old life can not sustain the strength that my new self demands to express. i am afraid that the life i planned out, will cease to exist, because i am listening to my healing heart and it is leading me to more healing, health and sacred care.
.
i am afraid that one more day passes and i do not engage with my true self and celebrate that every waking pain i have known has been a gift, and that gift has lead me to a place of knowing myself and finding myself to be enough, just as i am.
.
so...my fear subsides. and i continue to move forward trusting that we are all fearfully and wonderfully made....no matter where you are....what you are fighting for...i hope this is your truth todayâ¤ï¸
.
.

text:
itâ€™s fearless friday!  this pic is really old yet i keep it propped up by my desk as a reminder that i can do things even if theyâ€™re scary.
.
this pic was taken in ixtapa right after i went parasailing.  i had been watching others do it for a few days and wanted to try it because it looked really cool, but i hesitated because it also looked scary.  i would have to trust the boat driver to not take me too far out, iâ€™d have to trust that my landing would be safe, iâ€™d have to trust that there wouldnâ€™t be any sharks when i landed....i remember waiting in line and almost left the line a few times.  i was scared.  this was something new to me, it was unknown, and it was something i would have no control over once i was in the air.
.
i loved it!!! the view was breathtaking.  i felt free.  it was relaxing and exhilarating at the same time.  i didnâ€™t want my time in the air to end.  i was sooo glad i stayed in line and waited my turn.  i was so glad i didnâ€™t let my fears take over and get the best of me.  how disappointing it would have been to have missed this experience.
.
when iâ€™m stepping in the unknown, trying something new, needing to trust myself or others, not being able to control a situation and needing to go with the flow, i look at this picture and remember i can do it, i can trust myself and my intuition, i donâ€™t need to have the control or know the outcome in advance, and that sometimes things we really want are a little scary.
.
take a moment today to think about what fear is holding you back.  how can you move forward and not let your fear(s) set you back?  have a great day - itâ€™s friday! ğŸ’œ

text:
the first ever black male summit @carnegiemellon is happening next weekend, starting with a keynote lecture from dr. derrick brooms on friday feb 1, and a daylong summit on saturday feb 2.

the summit will feature workshops and panel discussions led by black male cmu students and staff and clinical professionals, including: black manhood 101, black mental health, black men and #metoo, and black male sense of belonging at cmu. this event will serve as the founding weekend of a black male initiative and annual summit.

register now: tinyurl.com/cmu-bms-register

all summit events will be held in the cohon university center and are open to everyone at cmu. breakfast and lunch will be served the day of the summit. 
the keynote lecture is open to the general public and will be followed by a networking reception in the center for student diversity and inclusion.

for questions about the summit and how to get involved in the initiative, email kevin jarbo (kjarbo@cmu.edu)

one in three women experience violence in their lifetime, across all social status, class, race, country or age group. for many of them, the #metoo moment hasnâ€™t come yet, because speaking out can have fatal consequences, and survival is a long and complicated journey.â €
*a un study of 10,000 men in asia and the pacific, released in 2013, found that overall nearly half of those men interviewed reported using physical and/or sexual violence against a female partner, ranging from 26 percent to 80 percent across the sites studied.  nearly a quarter of men interviewed reported perpetrating rape against a woman or girl, ranging from 10 percent to 62 percent across the sites. #gillette #metoo #hearmetoo #planet5050

text:
forgiveness is a word that can cause a guttural-defense reaction,
especially for those that have been mistreated or wronged
there are many reasons why a woman would be resistant to embrace and forgive her brothers,
and even to unite with her masculine-self within
and there are many reasons why a man would be hesitant to trust and open to his sisters,
and even to unite with his feminine-self within 
but,
forgiveness itself is something beautiful.
forgiveness is the ability to hold compassion for another soul,
to see the divinity in their being
to acknowledge the beat of their heart
to recognize that they were a baby once, just like you
and they will grow old someday, just like you
forgiveness is to humanize that which we have demonized
it is to face beings that have been cast as monsters,
and to simply see their being-ness within,
it is to acknowledge the untouchable innocence of their soul-spark 
please hear and digest:
forgiveness is entirely different from justification,
as it is about the being and not about their action(s)
forgiveness does not justify abuse, rape, cruelty, bullying, degradation, objectification, injustice, or any toxic behavior
forgiveness for a being and protest/rage towards their actions can unequivocally coexist
we can acknowledge the never-lost innocence of an individualâ€™s soul,
while deeming their human action as guilty 
grant yourself the gift of coexisting contradiction
know that you can despise an action and simultaneously forgive a being 
forgiveness is a decision based in energetic shift
and because this shift takes place in the soul realm,
forgiveness does not always need to be reflected in human word or action
it is more than enough that forgiveness be demonstrated by a shift in your own heart space,
and forgiveness does not need to be proven by giving your time to abusers, staying in dangerous or triggering situations, or through any other external words, commitments or behaviors âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨ my theme word of 2019 is forgiveness, is hoâ€™oponopono. on feb 5th iâ€™m speaking at a @projectfword event that explores the ways forgiveness may belongs in the #metoo movement, according to survivors. more details to come ğŸ’š

text:
this week iâ€™ve been reflecting on my role as a researcher. i identify as a woman. i identify as an intersectional feminist. i identify, and have reclaimed the word, as a fat woman.(but thatâ€™s another post for another time.) the thing is i have been all too aware of this while researching. almost daily iâ€™m talking to men about two very touchy subjects - masculinity and mental health.

with gender power dynamics i undoubtedly influence their answers - they may not want to offend me and likewise, they may be more open with me as a woman. either way iâ€™ve worked hard to be a researcher first, and a woman second.

my first mistake was separating the two. my second was putting my gender in the backseat.

the longer i do this, the more important i believe the female perspective is. from mothers raising boys to teenage girls having their first relationship. we shape men and men shape us.

when i first spoke to my tutor about being an intersectional feminist researcher (i know itâ€™s a mouthful) she told me to find others. i couldnâ€™t. it made me uncertain.

now iâ€™m certain. so iâ€™m thinking of collecting womenâ€™s stories about menâ€™s mental health too. what do you think? is that a good idea?

happy friday! ğŸšğŸ’¨ğŸ¶â˜€ï¸

signed,
wagent x

words for the world:
me too part 5. 
a series. .
.
.
parties and fake friends. .
.
this was all fun and games,
and you are acting 
just the same as me.
why is it that only i 
am being told 
i am a dramatic whore?
are you not sleeping with
3 different men and 
two of which
you are tempting to 
be unfaithful.
so why am i 
the uselss whore?
how could you tell me 
in one breath that 
i am strong and 
you admire me,
then turn around and 
throw me under fire 
so no one notices you
and all that you do. 
you are weak. 
you always were. 
i just wish i caught that
before i let your words stick
to my heart. -mahriyah willow

stop. think. ask. listen. analyse. consent is complicated like all human behaviour. create an open space with your partner/s to be able to comfortably have a dialogue. do not make assumptions on the other personâ€™s behalf.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: movies watched in 2019. revisited black swan. itâ€™s a film that in a post #metoo world gives me the ickiest vibes, and for all its technical bravura and well crafted, pressure-cooker atmosphere, i cannot help but feel very uncomfortable about how much of the internalised misogyny that permeates ninaâ€™s psychology is intentional commentary or the unconscious purging of aronofskyâ€™s own issues with women. nevertheless, nina is a character who has always resonated with me; her desire for perfection, fear of failure, utter craving for approval and the lack of self love that these things all stem from. i cannot help but feel a personal connection with her in some twisted way.

text:
**warning: this a very long, very personal, and very emotionally charged post** i usually don't share my opinion about abortion because people are so quick to anger and judgement without even listening/thinking these days..but with all the posts i've been reading lately i can't hold it in anymore. let me make it clear that i do not personally believe in abortion. but as a result of my own personal experiences, i cannot judge another woman for her personal choice. 
i remember just like it was yesterday. running out of an unfamiliar building. running down a street that i'd never been down before. no shoes. no phone. turning into a building with a light on and pounding on the window, with tears streaming down my face, until someone finally opened the door. i was so scared, paranoid, hurt, ashamed.. and then angry.. and then empty and depressed. i was lucky enough not to have gotten pregnant. but it was hard enough as it was. 
so instead of just voicing our opinions against women who make the decision to have an abortion, how about we raise our voices in support of other programs?! more programs to support adoption over abortion. more programs and support groups for women who need mental and emotional support during and after their pregnancy.  people say, "just give it up for adoption" like that will solve everything. no matter what they choose, adoption or abortion, they're still left with what happened to them long after.
 and it's not just victims of sexual assault that need support. it could be young women who are scared and they may not have the support of family or a spouse/partner. or there could be other complications that lead them to feel like they need to abort their pregnancy. 
again, i'm not saying i support abortion. but i do believe that we should be more empathetic and proactive in supporting these women instead of just passing judgment. â¤
#believewomen #metoo #yesallwomen

everything is a thing. itâ€™s exhausting.

quanada cites power of #metoo following ernst confessionquincy, ill. â€”Â the highest ranking female republican in the senate said thursday she was mentally and physically abused by her ex-husband.senator joni ernst shared she was forced to reveal details of her private pain -- after her divorce documents became public.the iowa republican has also revealed she's a rape survivor.khqa met with the quincy area network against domestic abuse also known as quanada today.executive director megan duesterhaus said the senator's experience is one that many women face.she says the metoo movement shows power in numbers and the perversity of domestic abuse.â€œwhat we just keep seeing is that sexual violence is everywhere and it doesn't discriminate. it happens to people from all walks of life. if it could happen to a well-known legislator, it could happen to your second-grade teacher,â€ duesterhaus said.duesterhaus stresses that sharing your story is not for everyone and to come forward when you're ready. original article source...

text:
â€œchildhood trauma is relational trauma... you can't heal relational trauma by yourself. it has to be healed in relationships.â€ - joyelle brandt.

relational trauma requires relational repair. repeatedly in the testimony of survivors there comes a moment when a sense of connection is restored by another person's unaffected display of generosity. something in themselves that the victims believed to be irretrievably destroyed - faith, decency, courage - is reawakened by an example of common altruism. mirrored in the actions of others or someone, the survivor recognizes and reclaims a lost part of herself or himself.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
â¡ï¸grim reality of why the west's white race is now a dying breed

white women in western societies are producing on average fewer, sometimes much fewer, than 2.1 children per woman - the number of children required for the maintenance of a population. as things stand, therefore, the white race in the west is a dying breed.

harvard university analyzed dna from thousands of americans who described themselves as being part of a singular racial group. the results, published in the american journal of human genetics, revealed that almost 4% of participants who identify as white have "hidden" african ancestry. 
https://mic.com/articles/106856/geneticists-have-found-something-surprising-about-the-dna-of-white-people
ğŸ‘±â€â™‚ï¸
if your heritage is non-african, you are part neanderthal, according to a new study in the july issue of molecular biological magazine.
ğŸ‘‡
neanderthal inbreeding has left humans weaker: non-africans have lower fitness levels due to 'genetic burden'.
genetic analysis has revealed that mutations built up in neanderthal dna over time, due to inbreeding.

text:
what if law enforcement talked to people who have been robbed the same way they often treat people who have been sexually assaulted?

a new video written and directed by cynthia kao shows how absurd common responses to sexual assault allegations seem within the context of a robbery.

in the video, two police officers question a man about a laptop stolen from his home and continually suggest that the robbery was his fault â€” a nod to the victim-blaming so common in sexual assault cases. â€œflashing your goods for all the world to see? kinda sounds like you were asking for it,â€ one cop says when the man says his laptop was in front of a window. 
the officers also ask if the victim had been drinking question the â€œlack of evidence,â€ and tell the robbed man that filing a report will only cause more trouble. sexual assault survivors commonly hear these questions from police officers, which in turn discourages them from charging their assailants or even reporting the assault in the first place.

we wouldnâ€™t blame someone for becoming a laptop-theft victim â€” donâ€™t assault survivors deserve the same? - huffington post

#speakout #nomore #timesup #justice #metoo #endsexualassault #stopvictimblaming #supportingsurvivors #whyyoushouldreport

text:
this is a huge huge lesson that over the years i have struggled to learn. i always believed that if i could make other people happy by giving then i would find my own happiness. but oh how the tide has changed when i finally realised that actually i was in charge of my own happiness, that only i could truly make myself happy, and i was on a severe pathway of self destruction. i worked in this place where i always gave, my time, my heart, my energy ect, a place where i considered the people in it my friends and family. people were more than happy to take take take, but when i left only 1 person took the time to actually see how we were doing, and i got to realised that i was just being used again. into this new year i am so glad that i have the few people around that i do, how they are so genuine, and mean the world to me, the true meaning of friendship. i am also grateful for the people i have met, the places i've been, and the lessons that i have been able to learn along the way, because without them i wouldn't be the person i am today, that walked through hell and extinguished the flames, have the peace i hold within, the happiness that i have learned to create myself, and the beauty of true friendship.

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnnâ€™s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from koganâ€™s app may not have been completely deleted. koganâ€™s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

gop is dead. gop remains dead. and we have killed him. how shall we comfort ourselves, the murderers of all murderers? what was holiest and mightiest of all that the world has yet owned has bled to death under our knives: who will wipe this blood off us? what water is there for us to clean ourselves? what festivals of atonement, what sacred games shall we have to invent? is not the greatness of this deed too great for us? must we ourselves not become gods simply to appear worthy of it?

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

text:
one of my patients, who is in her late 70s, has written an article on my website about why she is still taking hrt. 
she states â€œthere has been so much media coverage about #metoo but now we must campaign for â€˜renewed life in middle ageâ€™â€.
the full article can be read here - https://www.menopausedoctor.co.uk/menopause/to-take-or-not-to-take-that-is-the-question
all the current menopause guidelines are clear that women can take hrt for as long as the benefits outweigh any risks. there is no upper age limit nor maximum length of time for taking hrt. 
i personally will never stop taking my hrt as i worry about osteoporosis and stopping hrt will then increase my risk of osteoporosis. 
taking hrt needs to be an individualised choice which is often easier to make when women are given correct, evidence based and non-biased information. 
#menopause #womenshealth #hormones #hrt #empoweringwomen #knowledgeispower #guidelines

text:
good morning long beach! itâ€™s a new day and there are new hopes and dreams in my heart.

after a few weeks without my cell service, iâ€™m feeling reflective. i was able to negotiate with my cell provider to remove my abusive exâ€™s cell phone charge from my phone line. iâ€™m feeling thankful for the strength and resilience to do that. some of us are only a few hundred dollars away from ending up in collections, but iâ€™m not going to stay here. watch me!

when youâ€™re escaping an abusive relationship it will cost you everything. everything. but it will be worth it.

finances, of going from a two family income to a single family income. relationships with family and friends who only saw the highlight reels and donâ€™t understand how this could happen because he is such a nice guy. yeah, thatâ€™s why i married him. romantic love, because honestly i do love and will always love him, but when the authorities tell you never to get back together with someone because one of you will end up dead, you listen for the sake of your kids. the institutionalized church family. iâ€™ll leave it at that. watching my kids grieve and not understand has been the hardest by far. by far! but you know? we canâ€™t protect our kids from pain and that isnt in the job description of being a parent. 
but you know? protecting them by teaching them resilience. providing for them. loving them. that is in the job description and i will keep doing that. 
mom is my most important title i will ever have and today and everyday, i am thankful to be raising resilient kids. we are going to be soooo good and someday i might write a book. but you know? if you think itâ€™s ok to be abusive, stop. you do you and get the help that is available! please! families work best when theyâ€™re together. but, this message is for those victims out there. there is someone reading this today that is counting that cost and iâ€™m going to tell you, go for it. do whatever it takes. it wonâ€™t be easy, but it will be worth it.

text:
i can help you heal and never worry about hpv & cervical dysplasia ever again// my dear sister,

there is nothing more that i want than for you to feel good and empowered in your body.

with the current political climate, this desire feels more like a war-cry.

from #metoo, the unveiling of sexual assault in hollywood and beyond, the womenâ€™s march and all the women coming out of the woodwork to express their truth, i truly feel like a global shift if occurring.

it is time for women to be sovereign in the bodyâ€™s experiences and choices.

it is time for women to reconnect to their bodies for their sake, and for the sake of all the women who came before who could not.

healing the cervix is healing our ancestral wounds, for all the memory of that which has penetrated us is stored in the cervix. that means, for thousands of generations our mothers and grandmothers stored their memories in their cervixes, but never had the chance to heal them.

this changes with us, and i can help you.

i know i can help you.

i can help you reconnect to your cervix and love your body in a way that you never knew possible.

i can help you become informed and aware of the health of your cervix, and how it relates to the health of your whole body and being.

i can help you feel empowered in your gynecological experiences so that you never feel disempowered, overcome, terrified or alone in the process.

you're not alone.

millions of women are experiencing this alongside you, and together, we can change the narrative and heal our disconnection to this very, very sacred body part.

and so please, dear sister, head to the link in my bio to learn how this information will transform your life and experience in the gynecologistâ€™s office.

i am sending out the war-cry.

are you ready to receive it?

with fervent love,

xoxo
denell

text:
it's your, check engine light on, too? in recovery, we need to take stock often of what's going on with us and why. in the process, we just might discover something new, even after years of recovery... during recovery group this week, i asked the ladies if they had ever avoided reaching out when they needed to. all but one had, which is shocking (women in recovery of any form often feel like a burden and bother). i was surprised, because i knew she wasn't reaching out early in recovery nearly as often as she needed, to me or the other women in group. so we got curious about that.

funny how the truth comes out... "i just didn't call you because i didn't want you to call me out! then i would have to work on it. ugh!" wait...wha?!?!?!? we all had a pretty good laugh, and the other women all nodded their heads or voiced agreement. it was a fun moment of bonding for all of us.

i think that's pretty common; we don't always want to be honest or take responsibility for ourselves right away. often as women, it goes deeper--we don't feel capable or worthy of a better life, so we stay stuck. maybe we don't even realize how happy we'll feel once we are really willing to change for the better and truly understand how our actions/beliefs/fears are causing the saddness, depression and anxiety.

so i got serious about how i might "not reach out" when it feels uncomfortable. after 19 years in recovery, there are still things i'd rather not think about (ahem, the budget or retirement....) often, the worry and avoidance is more troublesome than actually tackling the issue. therefore, i'll be balancing the checkbook today.

are you avoiding anything? if so, i want to challenge you to get clear on it, maybe even share what you are going to do here for a little accountability. then, get to it! you'll be so gald when it's over.

howlindsey doody

__
claiming this part of my identity because itâ€™s been such a part of me that i used to hate owning as part of me. i used to feel claiming the word survivor made me weak, because in my mind it meant admitting to all the times i felt so powerless & weak and because it ultimately meant acknowledging that yes, i was a victim of violence & it has impacted every aspect of my life.
__
claiming the word has made me realize the power in the word â€œsurvivorâ€ is about accepting the reality of what iâ€™ve been through & loving the parts of me who have been through hell & figured out how to survive under difficult circumstances.
â€”
i realized all the coping strategies i developed as a result of abuses iâ€™ve been through helped me in my past, one of which was silence, helped me make it out alive & to get by in the world & even when those chose not to help & when i tried to speak up as a child. but, silence no longer serves me or others suffering or those who are just unaware.
â€”
i will not censor myself or my story with silence.
__
i will continue speaking up, sharing my truth, my story in bigger & bolder ways with the strong intention to continue on my healing journey & sharing tools of empowerment & invite the world to heal because this phenomenon of abuse is a global issue i intend to help transmute in my lifetime with the power of truth & love.
__
i choose to be seen. be heard. be true. be love.
__

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

thatâ€™s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him â€œwe can take it.â€ no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but itâ€™s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then itâ€™s easy to come along for the ride. thereâ€™s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. theyâ€™re both just characters on the television.

thatâ€™s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. itâ€™s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. itâ€™s that weâ€™ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

thatâ€™s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him â€œwe can take it.â€ no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but itâ€™s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then itâ€™s easy to come along for the ride. thereâ€™s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. theyâ€™re both just characters on the television.

thatâ€™s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. itâ€™s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. itâ€™s that weâ€™ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text: 8:01pm a few hrs ago i had to make a call. i needed help. i dropped another plate and it set me off. both my hands have nerve damage from a domestic fight i was in a few years back. that fight followed a sexual trauma with the same person that still has me pretty fucked up...but for some specific reasons: i want to be over all of it. i swear on that shit. but i have permanent reminders of a lot of my pain. i drop a plate? it takes me to my darkest times. i want to be over all of it...but my friends hang out with him. i want to be over it. but he works in some of the same spaces as me and it makes it hard for me to. ive been told my words fuck up his rep...could ruin his life...could affect his career...his family. but what about mine? i want to get over it but my blatent cries for help were mocked. gossiped about. and i was shunned. i want to get over it but every single time i look at my face, i see physical reminders of my pain. i want to get over it but im angry that i wrap my arms around every.fucking.body. all the time...even when i barely have anything to give...and barely anyone wrapped their arms around me when i needed it. my self-worth took a downward plunge that i cant believe i came back from. i want to get over it but #metoo. i want to get over it but everywhere i turn people are talking about everyones pain from cosby to r kelly and how fucked up people are. theyre talking about how bad they feel for everyone that deals with verbal...emotional...physical...domestic...sexual abuse/trauma. ...feels like everyone but me. a few hours ago i had to make a call. because i needed help. i became angry about the men ive allowed to half love me (if that) bc i dont know what healthy love looks like. i became angry at myself for not demanding more for myself. i sat on my floor with a broken plate around me. just crying. so...a few hours ago i had to make a call. i needed help. and my friend said..."sit still...sit quietly...and forgive. its the only way out of this. you have to forgive him. you have to forgive them. ...and then...the most important part...you have to forgive you." i sat for an hour. forgiving. and i will continue to forgive. more loveğŸ–¤.

text:
mic test 1,2â€¦ 1,2. calling out all cheaters, calling you all out.

hard topic to talk about, and iâ€™ve been wanting to talk about it for years. iâ€™ve had sex with girls who were in relationships, a couple of them were married, the others in long term relationships. iâ€™m trying not to beat around the bush here. i donâ€™t want to muddle the word â€œsexâ€ with â€œsexual advancesâ€ as god knows iâ€™ve made plenty of those over my time (hey iâ€™ve had my fair share of girls making aggressive sexual advances at #metoo). with the girls: fact is i knew what i was doing felt wrong but i went there anyways. i talk a lot and ask a lot of questions. i prefer my emotions out rather than in. more than a few times iâ€™ve tried to bring up the deed in conversation but iâ€™m usually faced with 1 of 2 things; 1) iâ€™m made to feel silly for thinking anything of it! are you seriously saying youâ€™re feeling guilty right now?! um, yes? yes i am?! 2) iâ€™m introduced to the concept of â€œkeeping a secretâ€ something iâ€™ve never done and highly doubt i could ever do.

with the guys: iâ€™ve always had closer girl friends than guy friends. i still do. i consider my friends wives to be my mates. it hurts then to see what iâ€™ve seen on overseas trips with the boys. when i confronted the guys about the issue i expressed that i was single, which somewhat gave me the right to do whatever i wanted, but you guys are married, with children! the response? who the fuck are you to judge justin? floored. speechless. i get it.

back to the girls again: i crossed the line once and admitted to one of the girls what her guy was doing. what was the response? shut the fuck up justin i donâ€™t want to hear it!!! back to the guys again: just last year a mate was parading that he got a bare back blow job overseas. congratulations man, you just gave your kids an std.

iâ€™m talking about it because everyone world wide seems to think that encouraging conversation is a great way to begin resolving big issues, but from what iâ€™ve learned from experience; talking is the last thing the guilty want to do.

â£
goal: reduce binge eating with a food diary, talk about my feelings instead of eating them, consistently show up for 6 weeks of workouts (5 days per week), talk to myself with a whole lot of love and grace. â£
â£
i would say the work iâ€™ve done over the last 6 weeks has been some of my best. particularly because my goals were not related to a number on the scale or the size of my pants. â£
â£
coach stephie juice tip: shift the focus of your fitness goals from the symptom to the issue. the issue of weight gain is not typically the problem, the problem is what is causing it... poor diet, inconsistency, binge eating, stress? those are the things that need to be tackled. otherwise... you will just keep getting the same result and youâ€™ll likely never be satisfied for more than a short term few moments when you hit the magic number on the scale. â£
â£
retrain your brain to support your life in a healthy and loving way. â£
you deserve that. and if you want to lose weight or wear a smaller pant size thatâ€™s ok! but you still deserve to love yourself through the process. â£
â£
goal setting is kind of my thing, if you need help just ask! and in the mean time check out my insta stories to see my favorite workout gear! â£

text: did you know that the #metoo movement didnâ€™t begin with a celebrity tweet in 2017? it actually began 20 years earlier in 1997, when a 13 year old girl told tarana burke, a black woman, about being sexually abused. burke was haunted by the story. 10 years later, she founded a non profit organization to support sexual assault and harassment victims. she also founded a movement and named it metoo. a woman of color, a non celebrity, far from hollywood, originally coined the now familiar phrase.

text:
part one: the womenâ€™s locker room. .
.
. 
today after a glorious hour of cardio dance, followed by a soothing steam and shower, i was basking in my after workout wonder in the locker room. standing proudly in my panties, i tended to my hair, admired my body and sat atop the post workout mountain i had just climbed. success was surrounding me and i was so happy to feel liberated amongst my fellow women - to be with my body in a natural way. two effervescent girls were chatting, laughter was in the air and the place was abundant with endorphins. grateful. .
.
.

these two girls took a vulnerable turn, and one by one the ladies of the locker room lost their buzz. subconsciously, we all tuned in as they disclosed their realities. the energy from this conversation was seething. their pride, dignity, body and jobs had been stolen from them. one began to confide in the other about being a 19-year-old female with her 35-year-old senior manager harassing her. she felt she couldnâ€™t tell anyone at work and everything she was doing wasnâ€™t being taken seriously. he had crossed so many lines she had finally decided her only option was to quit. she was a server: beautiful, young, and condemned. her friend responded with sympathy and then began to remind her of a situation that happened to her at her last job, â€œremember when i had to quit my job at **** because my manager was doing the same thingâ€¦ it sucks but thatâ€™s just part of being a server.â€ photo credit: @skipischris

text:
part two:

at this point, i looked down and noticed my hands were shaking. i was in shock from anger and lifted my head to look around. the look on every single, silent, disturbed womanâ€™s face in the room was united. all inaudible, all together. the girls confiding hadnâ€™t noticed the darkness or depth that was being brought out of everyone through their disclosures. donâ€™t make eye contact. we cannot let anyone else see. this experience could not have, should not haveâ€¦ how did it happened to me. please. donâ€™t. remind. me. why. canâ€™t. i. breathe. with shaky hands and even shakier voice, i mustered the strength and peeked around the lockers to approach them. apprehensively, i apologized for intruding but said i just needed a moment of their time. i told them that it was not only unfair, but just fucking wrong what was happening and had happened to them. i told them there are tons of resources to help move through situations like this. i told them that they werenâ€™t alone, and if they needed resources or help, to take my contact information and that i could help connect them. then i told them that i understand whole heartedly if they donâ€™t want to say anything, but if you donâ€™t act at all, think of the other girls who will come after. you could see the lights come on in both their eyes. one of them said, â€œi had never even thought about that.â€ i told them i was there if they needed, then slunk away. i couldnâ€™t stomach saying much more as i could feel my throat closing and tears coming through as i finished speaking. .
.
.

text: very proud to be sharing this work created in collaboration with @micaela_mamede for her awe inspiring choreography performance at gibney dance, this is #maria2018. produced and performed by an ensemble of non-us immigrant women and allies, maria tells the all too common story of violence and silence immigrant women face. this whole project was made possible by micaela and her unwavering visual mission to share her own voice. she's since gained the support of the #healmetoo festival, a grassroots foundation working to heal victims of sexual violence by funding creative, therapeutic outlets for victims. please join us at the first ever nyc heal me too festival march 27-april 19, 2019. to learn more about their work, please follow @micaela_mamede and @healmetoofest and visit www.healmetoofest.com #metoo #womenshistorymonth #intimatepartnerviolence #healing - makeup by @batamakeup and cast: #danutapetrow-sek #emilyteller #hayetmoutfi, #krishnawashburn #malaikacambridge #maluavalos #mariasek #micaelamamede and #pearlbhatnagar - thank you ladies. xo

text:
when it comes to instagram, i feel like iâ€™m on xfactor and simon cowell is telling me iâ€™ve picked up a lot of bad habits â€“ that my posts are a bit â€˜cabaretâ€™. given that iâ€™ve only posted 14 times thereâ€™s a whiff of hyperbole in the air, but the overthinker in me can already tell that iâ€™m not really nailing this insta-lark. the great thing is, iâ€™ve decided not to care.
~

~

~
more recently, i had a toe curling read through my old facebook posts before i deleted my account. yet itâ€™s anachronistic to say these posts were silly or embarrassing because they ultimately reflected their era, a time when sarah wrote in the third person and poking people wasnâ€™t a #metoo moment.
~
ultimately, what iâ€™m trying to say is authenticity is better than perfection. thatâ€™s it. that is basically my white card to keep being a bit insta-shit and to use the insta-prefix even if itâ€™s a bit cabaret to do so.
~

text:
#throwbackthursday to a piece i created for @drawwithjazza 's pimp my classic cotm for february 2018
.
'#metoo - a twitter spear' is a modernised twist on raphael's "st. michael vanquishing satan"
.
art & concept description below:inspired to bring the relevance of a great good vs a great evil into the modern age, i thought alyssa milano's 2017 'metoo' twitter campaign that all began with a tweet asking people to speak up was a strong modern concept.
the point of 'metoo' is to shine a light on how widespread the issue is rather than call out a particular gender or individual.
thus the blinding light of the twitter 'spear' wielded by 'archangel' (@milano_alyssa) shines down and threatens to expose a figure i consider not to be person. i chose to embody the dangers of sexual harassment and assault in the form of a popular creepy pasta monster. something faceless but you know to be wary of it.
slenderman, known to abduct, traumatise and manipulate but not truly known in pop culture to kill was the ideal metaphor to replace lucifer. his hooked and grasping tentacles weave around the angel but are ultimately powerless against the light - cringing away at its touch as he is pinned to the ground.
.
#trixks #art #artistsoninstagram #digitalart #tbt #illustration #artchallenge #artoftheday #challenge #pimpmyclassic #fantasyart #slenderman #archangel #angel

text:
it's easy to get sucked into feeling like nothing can go right, especially if you've been in an abusive relationship. i know because i've been there. but guess what? you don't have to stay there. you deserve to live the best life possible. you deserve to have great experiences, a hopeful future, and plain ol' happiness. ğŸ˜€
the fact that you've been broken simply means that now you've been opened up to do more, accept more, love more and live more. embrace that!

text:
6 months ago i was at my worst. 6 months ago i was drowning everything that was ever given to me, literally and figuratively. i have never been so low or in so much pain in my life. i had never been treated as badly, or been in a worse place.

today i was able to wake up, get up,  go to work for 9 hours, and i had the time of my life. i'm happy. i have all i need at the moment, and i'm just thankful. i feel good about myself and it's only getting better!
cheers to accepting where we are. no matter where that is, and no matter what has happened to you. you can still be happy, because we're not defined by our past. ğŸ’™

p.s. we're also never defined by a diagnosis or an experience. you are you because you choose you. no one can tell you who you are.
#survivor #lymedisease #bpd #metoo #werule

text:
so, weâ€™re introducing you to this ğŸ‘‘ today. elon, a true icon, is dominating advocacy on maternal and infant justice. more about her below ğŸ‘‡ğŸ½ .
.
.
elon has been a birth doula since 2016, she came to doula work "accidentally" after being a home visitor for a local health department. through that experience she discovered that many women she provided services to were experiencing isolation during pregnancy and lacked positive psycho-social support lending to negative birth experiences. in partnership with local health department leadership and community members, she advocated for a dona community wide doula training and walked away with a practical skills and a deeper appreciation for the value of doula advocacy, particularly, for women of color.  while maintaining a private doula practice, elon has served as project coordinator, statewide speaker and consultant with a number of public health projects but finds her greatest joys in serving women as they transition into motherhood and fostering change in attitudes, policy and practice around pregnancy, labor and birth.  elon received her formal education from michigan state university where she studied physiology and health studies with a cognate in psychology. she is a certified parent educator (effective black parenting), certified childbirth educator (icea), trained in lamaze childbirth education and is a certified lactation consultant (alpp). .

text:
i was attacked on my way home from work tonight.

it was 6:20pm. iâ€™d just left the office and i was walking down a deserted road - the same road i walked down this morning, listening to @theguiltyfeminist podcast and feeling all #strongindependentwoman

a group of boys appeared around the corner. one of them came to within a few inches of me and screamed in my face, clearly looking for a reaction. this has happened before with the same group, so i knew what was coming and didnâ€™t react. but they hadnâ€™t got what they wanted, so the rest of the group gathered around me and started jeering and laughing. then one of them shoved me and i stumbled over. having succeeded in humiliating me sufficiently, they left.

iâ€™m not hurt. they were kids looking for a laugh, and trying to show off in front of their mates. as far as assault goes, i know this wasnâ€™t â€œthat badâ€ - people go through far, far worse.

and yet iâ€™m shaken. i just spent half an hour crying down the phone to my friend (and iâ€™m not normally a crier). i kept saying iâ€™m fine but iâ€™m not really fine. iâ€™ve been catcalled and whistled at, and iâ€™ve had people press against me on the tube, but this is the first time iâ€™ve received physical violence. this is not a list of feminist badges, this is the daily reality for many women around the world. iâ€™m astounded that itâ€™s 2019 and yet itâ€™s not safe to walk down the streets of london as a woman.

my friend encouraged me to share this on instagram, if nothing else to raise awareness that sexism is still very real, and feminism very much needed. now iâ€™m going to have a massive bowl of pasta and watch netflix. we are not the weaker sex. ğŸ’ªğŸ» #metoo

text:
everyday conversation is peppered with habitual sexism, conscious or unconscious. iâ€™m raising awareness because i owe it to my younger self, the self who was sexually harassed in the workplace. it started as banter, jokey comments, an arm around the shoulder, a bear hug, soft sweet talking, that became flirtatious. then it became shouting, passive aggressive, bullying, and controlling. picking me up from behind and squeezing me tight, in front of a room full of staff. blocking my exit from an office, and invading my personal space. it lasted 5 years. and i watched it happen to others. you may say why did i not do anything? each day i put on my armour and i found a way to keep going by blocking out what was really happening. i didnâ€™t know it was sexual harassment, this type of behaviour was accepted as normal. eventually i broke and i walked away from a profitable business. i will continue to raise awareness because everyday language peppered with habitual sexism, may lead to worse, if condoned and left to manifest. it happens. itâ€™s not ok. and itâ€™s ok to say itâ€™s not ok. .
.
